<subSubSection id="96BC651BB73028420D0DF55C38C1F484" pageId="21" pageNumber="411" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="DE193690B73028420D0DF55C38C1F484" blockId="21.[1366,2573,2333,2956]" pageId="21" pageNumber="411">
<emphasis id="ECD2EA82B73028420D0DF55C39E8F556" bold="true" box="[1367,1718,2765,2798]" pageId="21" pageNumber="411">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
CITES Appendix II. Classified as Endangered on The IUCN Red List (as 
<taxonomicName id="19A64D13B73028420DA6F5653853F4AD" authorityName="Pucheran" authorityYear="1845" box="[1532,1805,2804,2837]" class="Mammalia" family="Cebidae" genus="Cebus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Primates" pageId="21" pageNumber="412" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albifrons">C. albifrons versicolor</taxonomicName>
). The Varied White-fronted Capuchin probably occurs in Catatumbo Bari National Natural Park.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
